  "texts": [
    "Accordingly, we represent each corner kick situation as a graph, where each node corresponds to a player.",
    "The features associated with each node encode the movements (velocities and positions) and simple profiles (heights and weights) of on-pitch players at the timestamp when the corresponding corner kick was being taken by the attacking kicker (see the \"Methods\" section), and no information of ball movement was encoded.",
    "The graphs are fully connected; that is, for every pair of players, we will include the edge connecting them in the graph.",
    "Each of these edges encodes a binary feature, indicating whether the two players are on opposing teams or not.",
    "For each task, we generated the relevant dataset of node/edge/graph features and corresponding labels (Tables 1 and 2, see the \"Methods\" section)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}